[[Latin language|Latin]] word (from the Latin ''annus'', year), meaning:

*[[Annona]], plant [[genus]]

In the Roman empire
*[[Annona (goddess)]], personification of plenty, the produce of the yearly harvest, etc
* the [[corn dole]] to citizens, distributed from a [[statio annonae]]
* the produce of the year's [[harvest]]
* all means of subsistence, especially grain stored in the public [[granaries]] for provisioning the city
*The [[grain supply to the city of Rome]] in general
* the [[market price]] of commodities, especially corn
* a direct [[tax]] in kind, levied in [[republic]]an times in several provinces, chiefly employed in imperial times for distribution amongst officials and the support of the [[soldier]]y

